<concept id="concept-5429" xml:lang="en-us" class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">On the test runner machine</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><author translate="no" type="creator" class="- topic/author ">Windy Le &lt;windy.le@katalon.com&gt;</author><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><keywords class="- topic/keywords "/></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><p class="- topic/p "><note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                <ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">The test runner machine can be Windows, macOS or Linux.</li></ul>
            </note>While building your test script, make sure to have the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">WinAppDriver URL</codeph> point to the public IP address of the remote test machine. In the above example, it should be: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">http://192.168.37.95:4723/</codeph>.</p><p class="- topic/p ">The application file path is the absolute path to the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Windows Executable File (*.exe)</codeph> file of the remote test machine.<image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/3672749302fd26a6ee095ed5217b2be05aaf6d78/katalon-studio/docs/introduction-desktop-app-testing/KS-Windows-Remote-connection-3.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Remote connection in Katalon</alt></image></p></conbody></concept>